# Naval Air Facility Atsugi

**Naval Air Facility Atsugi** (厚木海軍飛行場, *Atsugi Kaigun-hikōjō*) ([IATA](/IATA_airport_code): NJA, [ICAO](/ICAO_airport_code): RJTA) is a joint Japan-US naval air base located in the cities of [Yamato](/Yamato,_Kanagawa) and [Ayase](/Ayase,_Kanagawa) in [Kanagawa Prefecture](/Kanagawa_Prefecture), [Japan](/Japan). It is the largest [United States Navy](/United_States_Navy) (USN) air base in the [Pacific Ocean](/Pacific_Ocean), and once housed all of the squadrons of [Carrier Air Wing Five](/Carrier_Air_Wing_Five) (CVW-5), which deploys with the American [aircraft carrier](/Aircraft_carrier) forward deployed to [Yokosuka Naval Base](/United_States_Fleet_Activities_Yokosuka).

During 2017 and 2018 the fixed-wing aircraft squadrons of CVW-5 relocated to [Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni](/Marine_Corps_Air_Station_Iwakuni) in western Japan leaving only its two helicopter squadrons at Atsugi. In addition to the two CVW-5 helicopter squadrons NAF Atsugi is also home to Helicopter Maritime Strike Squadron 51 ([HSM-51](/HSM-51)), which provides detachments of [MH-60R](/MH-60R) helicopters to forward deployed U.S. Navy [guided missile cruisers](/Guided_missile_cruiser), [guided missile destroyers](/Guided_missile_destroyer), and [frigates](/Frigate) at the nearby [Yokosuka Naval Base](/United_States_Fleet_Activities_Yokosuka). Service members stationed at Atsugi also work in conjunction with the former [Kamiseya Naval Radio Receiving Facility](/Naval_Support_Facility_Kamiseya).

[Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force](/Japan_Maritime_Self-Defense_Force) (JMSDF) forces at Atsugi are the Headquarters [Fleet Air Force](/Fleet_Air_Force_(JMSDF)), and [Fleet Air Wing 4](/Fleet_Air_Wing_4_(JMSDF)).

Despite its name, the base is 4 [nautical miles](/Nautical_mile) (7.4 km; 4.6 mi) east northeast from the [city of Atsugi](/Atsugi,_Kanagawa), and is not adjacent to the city.

